{"current_version": "0.1", "project": "Logging", "project_url": "https://eclipse-score.github.io/logging/", "versions": {"0.1": {"creator": {"program": "sphinx_needs", "version": "8.0.0"}, "needs": {"comp__data_router": {"belongs_to": ["feat__logging"], "content": "This is the data router component responsible for routing log messages to the appropriate sinks based on configuration and runtime conditions. It supports multiple logging backends and provides a flexible architecture for log management.", "docname": "score/datarouter/docs/index", "external_css": "external_link", "id": "comp__data_router", "implements": ["logic_arc_int__logging__logging"], "includes_back": ["mod__logging_repo", "mod_view_sta__logging__logging_view"], "lineno": 6, "safety": "ASIL_B", "section_name": "Data Router Documentation", "sections": ["Data Router Documentation"], "security": "YES", "status": "valid", "title": "Data Router", "type": "comp", "type_name": "Component"}, "comp__middleware": {"belongs_to": ["feat__logging"], "content": "This is the middleware component responsible for processing log messages before they are sent to the data router. It can perform tasks such as log formatting, filtering, and enrichment based on runtime context and configuration. The middleware is designed to be extensible, allowing for custom processing logic to be added as needed.", "docname": "score/mw/docs/index", "external_css": "external_link", "id": "comp__middleware", "implements": ["logic_arc_int__logging__logging"], "includes_back": ["mod__logging_repo", "mod_view_sta__logging__logging_view"], "lineno": 6, "safety": "ASIL_B", "section_name": "Middleware Documentation", "sections": ["Middleware Documentation"], "security": "YES", "status": "valid", "title": "Logging Middleware", "type": "comp", "type_name": "Component"}, "dec_rec__log__explicit_init": {"content": "Provide a library for explicit initialization of logging.\n\n**Context:**\n\nCurrently there are multiple approaches to logging initialization.\nRust frontend configuration is provided as code and requires explicit initialization before any logging starts.\nC++ configuration is lazily loaded on first use and based on a JSON file with path provided using environment variable.\n\nThis approach discrepancy makes it difficult to manage logging in multi-language environment.\nIssue can be solved by providing an explicit initialization library.\n\nSuch explicit logging initialization shall:\n\n- Initialize logging for Rust and C++ environments.\n- Handle configuration of all sub-components of the logging environment.\n- Provide interfaces to Rust and C++.\n\nExamples of use:\n\n- Initialize logging in Rust application:\n  - Rust logging frontend\n  - C++-based backend\n  - Rust/C++ log bridge\n- Initialize logging in C++ application utilizing Rust-based libraries:\n  - C++ logging\n  - Rust logging frontend utilized by libraries\n  - C++-based backend\n  - Rust/C++ log bridge\n\n**Consequences**\n\nSuch change will require design changes to middleware logging.\n\nIn Rust it is a common practice to explicitly initialize logging before any logging starts.\nThis is true to both `score_log` logging frontend and ubiquitous `log` crate that is a defacto standard for logging in Rust.\n\nMiddleware logging library is currently initialized lazily on first use, using JSON config file.\nIt is not possible to perform the initialization operation explicitly.\n\n**Justification for the Decision**\n\nExplicit logging initialization will simplify logging initialization in multi-language environments.", "context": "See below.", "decision": "TBA", "docname": "docs/design_decisions/explicit_init", "external_css": "external_link", "id": "dec_rec__log__explicit_init", "lineno": 4, "section_name": "Explicit initialization of logging", "sections": ["Explicit initialization of logging"], "status": "proposed", "title": "Explicit initialization of logging", "type": "dec_rec", "type_name": "Decision Record"}, "feat_arc_sta__logging__static_view": {"arch": {"diagram": "{{ draw_component(need(), needs) }}"}, "belongs_to": ["feat__logging"], "content": ".. needarch::\n   :scale: 50\n   :align: center\n\n   {{ draw_component(need(), needs) }}", "docname": "docs/features/logging/architecture/index", "external_css": "external_link", "fulfils": ["feat_req__logging__log_sources_user_app"], "id": "feat_arc_sta__logging__static_view", "includes": ["logic_arc_int__logging__logging"], "lineno": 30, "safety": "ASIL_B", "section_name": "Logging Feature Architecture", "sections": ["Logging Feature Architecture"], "security": "YES", "status": "valid", "title": "Feature Architecture Logging", "type": "feat_arc_sta", "type_name": "Feature & Feature Package Diagram"}, "mod__logging_repo": {"content": "The logging module provides a standardized logging framework for C++ and Rust projects using Bazel. It includes components for log routing and middleware processing, allowing for flexible log management and integration with various logging backends. The module is designed to be extensible and configurable to meet the needs of different applications and environments.", "docname": "docs/features/logging/architecture/index", "external_css": "external_link", "id": "mod__logging_repo", "includes": ["comp__data_router", "comp__middleware"], "lineno": 5, "safety": "ASIL_B", "section_name": "Logging Module View", "sections": ["Logging Module View"], "security": "YES", "status": "valid", "title": "Logging", "type": "mod", "type_name": "Module"}, "mod_view_sta__logging__logging_view": {"arch": {"diagram": "{{ draw_module(need(), needs) }}"}, "belongs_to": ["mod__logging"], "content": ".. needarch::\n   :scale: 50\n   :align: center\n\n   {{ draw_module(need(), needs) }}", "docname": "docs/features/logging/architecture/index", "external_css": "external_link", "id": "mod_view_sta__logging__logging_view", "includes": ["comp__data_router", "comp__middleware"], "lineno": 14, "section_name": "Logging Module View", "sections": ["L